name: **Illancrone**
description: Illancrone B695-103 Sheet 1 3.5km SSE of Aranmore. Unremarkable twin grassy tufts atop drumlinesque stony mounds, separated by the sea except at LW. Breeding Eider. The grid reference is for SE top. Land just NW of SE top. There is a beacon light on the SE. The ruin on the NW top was the holiday home of Saint Crona Beg, who summered here. SPA Barnacle Goose, Tern.
